'Provider obtains personal history (incl name, age, address, education, occupation)'
'Provider asks reason for visiting health facility'
'Provider asks whether there are lethargy, convulsions/convulsing now'
'Provider asks if the patient can drink or breastfeed.'
'Provider asks about frequency & Duration of cough.'
'Provider asks if there is difficulty in breathing, fast breathing, wheezing .'
'Provider asks whether mother or other family or community members have cough'
'Provider asks whether the stool contains blood or mucus.'
'Provider asks about fever – is there a pattern, duration, associated chills and/or rigors'
'Provider ask for HIV positivity in mother or child'
'Provider checks whether the patient is awake .If the patient is not awake, checks for consciousness/lethargy (try to wake)'
'Provider checks for signs of malnutrition – visible emaciation (marasmus or kwashiorkor), pallor (anemia), oedema. Measure MUAC'
'Provider weighs the patient. Checks weight on a growth chart.'
'Provider assesses the respiratory system – counts breaths, checks for chest indrawing, stridor, wheezing, listens to breath sounds.'
'Provider checks for dehydration – looks for sunken eyes, pinches the skin, offers the patient water if awake.'
'Provider takes blood sample for rapid diagnostic test or microscopy in the laboratory.'
'Provider counsels caregiver on proper dosage (no. of  doses/days, side effects)'
'Provider gives first dose of oral medicine on site'
